Date: 9/11/1899
Source: Otago Witness
Author:
Vol / Page: 39
Edition:
Quote: The naturally careless or, to use the shepherd's term, "slack" dog can never be taught to perform like this, though he may up to a certain stage be infinitely less trouble than the strong-eyed, keen one, but, then, no matter what amount of trouble is taken with him, he always requires to be kept at high pressure in training to keep him up to the mark, whereas with the other, once perfect always so.
